# Axle Grid Event Management v6  
## Fully Documented & Public Version
To setup an Axle account use link https://vpp.axle.energy/landing/grid?ref=R-JQDOUROD
---

## Overview

This Home Assistant automation manages a **Fox ESS battery system** during **Axle VPP export events**.

It automatically:

- Tracks Axle event publication
- Calculates battery energy requirements
- Pre-charges the battery if required
- Manages inverter operating modes
- Temporarily reduces heat pump demand
- Sends **fully diagnostic emails** at each lifecycle stage

Everything is driven by **Axle’s API updates** and **Home Assistant helpers**.

---

## Prerequisites

Before using this automation, you **must** set up the following in Home Assistant.

---

### 1. Input Datetime Helpers

Create **three input_datetime helpers**:

- `input_datetime.axle_event_prep_time`
- `input_datetime.axle_event_start_trigger`
- `input_datetime.axle_event_end_trigger`

These helpers are used as **time-based triggers** to manage the Axle event lifecycle.

---

### 2. Email / Notification Integration

This automation sends **HTML diagnostic emails** at each major lifecycle stage.

- A **Gmail integration** is assumed
- Notification service format used:
notify.first-part-of-email_gmail_com

If you use a different notification platform:

- Replace **all `notify.XYZ` actions** in the automation
- Keep the **message content unchanged**

### 3. Axle VPP Integration

Install the Axle integration via **HACS**:

https://github.com/deanhalllincoln/ha-axle-vpp


This integration provides the following entities:

- `sensor.axle_start_time`
- `sensor.axle_end_time`
- `sensor.axle_import_export`

Without this integration, the automation will not function.

### 4. Inverter Integration (Fox ESS Modbus)

This automation assumes **Fox ESS Modbus** entities are available, including:

- Battery SOC sensor
- Inverter operating mode selector
- Maximum SOC number entity
- Force charge power number entity

If you use a different inverter:

- Replace these entities with equivalents from your system
- Keep the underlying logic intact

---

### 5. Heat Pump / Large Load Control

This automation temporarily reduces household demand during export events to maximise grid export.

- Written for **Daikin Altherma**
- Uses the following entity:
climate.altherma_room_temperature

If you use:

- A different heat pump
- An EV charger
- An immersion heater
- Or other large electrical loads

Modify the relevant `climate.set_temperature` (or equivalent) actions to suit your system.

---

Full script (fully commented) below copy and paste in to a new automation in Home Assistant and make the modifications as your system requires.













alias: Axle Grid Event Management v6
description: |
  PUBLIC / FULLY DOCUMENTED VERSION

  This automation manages a Fox ESS battery during Axle VPP EXPORT events.

  It combines TWO previously separate automations:
    • Axle helper maintenance
    • Event lifecycle management

  ------------------------------------------------------------
  EVENT LIFECYCLE
  ------------------------------------------------------------
  0) Axle publishes or updates event times
       - Update helper datetimes

  1) Event published
       - Send full diagnostic email

  2) Prep time (1 hour before event)
       - Calculate energy requirements
       - Determine minimum SOC floor
       - Force charge if required
       - Send prep email

  3) Battery SOC reaches prep floor
       - Stop force charging automatically
       - Restore normal inverter mode
       - NO email sent

  4) Event start
       - Switch inverter to Force Discharge
       - Reduce heat pump demand
       - Send start email

  5) Event end
       - Restore inverter mode
       - Restore heat pump temperature
       - Send finished email

  SOC-triggered runs NEVER send emails.
  They exist only to stop force charging safely.

mode: single

############################################################
# TRIGGERS
############################################################
triggers:

  # Axle publishes or updates event timing
  - trigger: state
    entity_id:
      - sensor.axle_start_time
      - sensor.axle_end_time

  # Detect event publication (helper update)
  - trigger: state
    entity_id: input_datetime.axle_event_start_trigger

  # Time-based lifecycle triggers
  - trigger: time
    at: input_datetime.axle_event_prep_time

  - trigger: time
    at: input_datetime.axle_event_start_trigger

  - trigger: time
    at: input_datetime.axle_event_end_trigger

  # Battery SOC updates (logic-only)
  - trigger: state
    entity_id: sensor.foxinvertermodbus_battery_soc

############################################################
# CONDITIONS – GLOBAL SAFETY GATES
############################################################
conditions:

  # Ensure Axle event times exist and are valid
  - condition: template
    value_template: |
      {{ states('sensor.axle_start_time') not in ['', 'unknown', 'unavailable']
         and states('sensor.axle_end_time') not in ['', 'unknown', 'unavailable']
         and as_timestamp(states('sensor.axle_end_time'))
            > as_timestamp(states('sensor.axle_start_time')) }}

  # Only act on EXPORT events
  - condition: template
    value_template: "{{ states('sensor.axle_import_export') | lower == 'export' }}"

############################################################
# ACTIONS
############################################################
actions:

  ##########################################################
  # VARIABLES & CALCULATIONS
  ##########################################################
  - variables:

      # Convert Axle event times into timestamps
      event_start_ts: "{{ as_timestamp(states('sensor.axle_start_time')) }}"
      event_end_ts: "{{ as_timestamp(states('sensor.axle_end_time')) }}"

      # Current time
      now_ts: "{{ as_timestamp(now()) }}"

      # Seconds remaining until event start
      seconds_until_event_start: "{{ event_start_ts - now_ts }}"

      # Event duration in hours
      event_duration_hours: "{{ ((event_end_ts - event_start_ts) / 3600) | float(3) }}"

      ######################################################
      # USER CONFIGURATION SECTION
      ######################################################

      # Total battery capacity (kWh)
      battery_capacity_kwh: 20.72        # CHANGE FOR YOUR SYSTEM

      # Minimum SOC reserve (%)
      min_soc_percent: 10                # CHANGE FOR YOUR SYSTEM

      # Maximum export power (kW)
      inverter_max_export_kw: 5          # CHANGE FOR YOUR SYSTEM

      # Maximum force charge power (kW)
      max_charge_power_kw: 5             # CHANGE FOR YOUR SYSTEM

      ######################################################
      # DERIVED BATTERY VALUES
      ######################################################

      usable_capacity_kwh: "{{ battery_capacity_kwh * (1 - min_soc_percent / 100) }}"

      battery_soc_number: "{{ states('sensor.foxinvertermodbus_battery_soc') | float(0) }}"

      battery_energy_available_usable_kwh: |
        {{ [((battery_soc_number - min_soc_percent) / 100)
             * battery_capacity_kwh, 0] | max }}

      ######################################################
      # EVENT ENERGY REQUIREMENTS
      ######################################################

      energy_battery_during_event_kwh: "{{ inverter_max_export_kw * event_duration_hours }}"

      buffer_multiplier: |
        {% if event_duration_hours <= 1 %}
          1.10
        {% elif event_duration_hours >= 3 %}
          1.25
        {% else %}
          1.20
        {% endif %}

      total_required_with_buffer_kwh: "{{ energy_battery_during_event_kwh * buffer_multiplier }}"

      energy_deficit_kwh: "{{ total_required_with_buffer_kwh - battery_energy_available_usable_kwh }}"

      energy_deficit_kwh_positive: "{{ [energy_deficit_kwh, 0] | max }}"

      ######################################################
      # SOC TARGETS
      ######################################################

      desired_soc_percent_raw: |
        {{ min_soc_percent
           + (total_required_with_buffer_kwh / battery_capacity_kwh * 100) }}

      desired_soc_percent: "{{ [desired_soc_percent_raw, 100] | min | round(1) }}"

      prep_soc_floor_percent: |
        {% if event_duration_hours <= 1 %}
          50
        {% elif event_duration_hours <= 2 %}
          75
        {% else %}
          100
        {% endif %}

      final_required_charge_power_kw_clamped: |
        {% if energy_deficit_kwh_positive > 0
              or battery_soc_number < prep_soc_floor_percent %}
          {{ max_charge_power_kw }}
        {% else %}
          0
        {% endif %}

      ######################################################
      # ENTITY REFERENCES (CHANGE IF REQUIRED)
      ######################################################

      fox_operating_mode_entity: select.foxinvertermodbus_work_mode
      fox_max_soc_entity: number.foxinvertermodbus_max_soc
      fox_force_charge_power_entity: number.foxinvertermodbus_force_charge_power

      email_target: XXXXXXXXX@gmail.com

      ######################################################
      # FULL DIAGNOSTIC EMAIL BODY
      ######################################################
      email_message_diagnostic: >
        Axle Grid Event – Full Diagnostic Report<br><br>
        <b>Event Timing</b><br>
        Event start time: {{ states('sensor.axle_start_time') }}<br>
        Event end time: {{ states('sensor.axle_end_time') }}<br>
        Event duration (hours): {{ event_duration_hours | round(2) }}<br>
        Seconds until event start: {{ seconds_until_event_start | round(0) }}<br><br>

        <b>Battery Status</b><br>
        Battery SOC: {{ battery_soc_number | round(2) }} %<br>
        Battery capacity: {{ battery_capacity_kwh }} kWh<br>
        Min SOC reserve: {{ min_soc_percent }} %<br>
        Usable energy available: {{ battery_energy_available_usable_kwh | round(2) }} kWh<br>
        Desired SOC for event: {{ desired_soc_percent }} %<br>
        Prep SOC floor: {{ prep_soc_floor_percent }} %<br>
        Energy deficit: {{ energy_deficit_kwh | round(2) }} kWh<br>
        Charge power requested: {{ final_required_charge_power_kw_clamped }} kW<br><br>

        <b>Helpers</b><br>
        Prep time: {{ states('input_datetime.axle_event_prep_time') }}<br>
        Event start helper: {{ states('input_datetime.axle_event_start_trigger') }}<br>
        Event end helper: {{ states('input_datetime.axle_event_end_trigger') }}<br><br>

        <b>Fox ESS</b><br>
        Inverter mode: {{ states(fox_operating_mode_entity) }}<br>
        Max SOC: {{ states(fox_max_soc_entity) }} %<br>
        Force charge power: {{ states(fox_force_charge_power_entity) }} kW<br><br>

        Trigger source: {{ trigger.entity_id if trigger.entity_id is defined else 'time-based' }}

############################################################
# EVENT LOGIC (CHOOSE)
############################################################
  - choose:

      # Axle event updated → update helpers
      - conditions:
          - condition: template
            value_template: |
              {{ trigger.platform == 'state'
                 and trigger.entity_id in
                    ['sensor.axle_start_time','sensor.axle_end_time'] }}
        sequence:
          - variables:
              prep_ts: "{{ event_start_ts - 3600 }}"
          - action: input_datetime.set_datetime
            target:
              entity_id: input_datetime.axle_event_prep_time
            data:
              timestamp: "{{ prep_ts }}"
          - action: input_datetime.set_datetime
            target:
              entity_id: input_datetime.axle_event_start_trigger
            data:
              timestamp: "{{ event_start_ts }}"
          - action: input_datetime.set_datetime
            target:
              entity_id: input_datetime.axle_event_end_trigger
            data:
              timestamp: "{{ event_end_ts }}"

      # Event published email
      - conditions:
          - condition: template
            value_template: "{{ trigger.entity_id == 'input_datetime.axle_event_start_trigger' }}"
        sequence:
          - action: notify.XXXXXXXXX_gmail_com
            data:
              title: Axle event published
              message: "{{ email_message_diagnostic }}"
              target: "{{ email_target }}"

      # Prep time
      - conditions:
          - condition: template
            value_template: "{{ trigger.entity_id == 'input_datetime.axle_event_prep_time' }}"
        sequence:
          - choose:
              - conditions:
                  - condition: template
                    value_template: |
                      {{ energy_deficit_kwh_positive > 0
                         or battery_soc_number < prep_soc_floor_percent }}
                sequence:
                  - action: select.select_option
                    target:
                      entity_id: "{{ fox_operating_mode_entity }}"
                    data:
                      option: Force Charge
                  - action: number.set_value
                    target:
                      entity_id: "{{ fox_max_soc_entity }}"
                    data:
                      value: "{{ desired_soc_percent }}"
                  - action: number.set_value
                    target:
                      entity_id: "{{ fox_force_charge_power_entity }}"
                    data:
                      value: "{{ final_required_charge_power_kw_clamped }}"
          - action: notify.XXXXXXXXX_gmail_com
            data:
              title: Axle event prep started
              message: "{{ email_message_diagnostic }}"
              target: "{{ email_target }}"

      # Stop force charge when prep floor reached
      - conditions:
          - condition: template
            value_template: |
              {{ trigger.entity_id == 'sensor.foxinvertermodbus_battery_soc'
                 and battery_soc_number >= prep_soc_floor_percent
                 and states(fox_operating_mode_entity) == 'Force Charge'
                 and now_ts >= as_timestamp(states('input_datetime.axle_event_prep_time'))
                 and now_ts < event_start_ts }}
        sequence:
          - action: number.set_value
            target:
              entity_id: "{{ fox_force_charge_power_entity }}"
            data:
              value: 0
          - action: select.select_option
            target:
              entity_id: "{{ fox_operating_mode_entity }}"
            data:
              option: Feed-in First

      # Event start
      - conditions:
          - condition: template
            value_template: "{{ trigger.entity_id == 'input_datetime.axle_event_start_trigger' }}"
        sequence:
          - action: select.select_option
            target:
              entity_id: "{{ fox_operating_mode_entity }}"
            data:
              option: Force Discharge
          - action: climate.set_temperature
            target:
              entity_id: climate.altherma_room_temperature
            data:
              temperature: 16
          - action: notify.XXXXXXXXX_gmail_com
            data:
              title: Axle event started
              message: "{{ email_message_diagnostic }}"
              target: "{{ email_target }}"

      # Event end
      - conditions:
          - condition: template
            value_template: "{{ trigger.entity_id == 'input_datetime.axle_event_end_trigger' }}"
        sequence:
          - action: select.select_option
            target:
              entity_id: "{{ fox_operating_mode_entity }}"
            data:
              option: Feed-in First
          - action: climate.set_temperature
            target:
              entity_id: climate.altherma_room_temperature
            data:
              temperature: 22
          - action: notify.XXXXXXXXX_gmail_com
            data:
              title: Axle event finished
              message: "{{ email_message_diagnostic }}"
              target: "{{ email_target }}"
